{
  "text": "One-way reservation is used in OBS networks as it is assumed that the average data burst transmission time can be much shorter than the propagation delay between nodes [CITATION_1] . Also, the processing time T cp of the control packets at intermediate nodes can be significant when compared to the transmission time of the data bursts. In these situations, feedback acknowledgment (two-way reservation) approach will be very inefficient. Using one-way reservation, the large propagation delay between nodes will no longer be a major concern for system performance. OBS networks can therefore perform better than the connection-oriented wavelength-routed optical networks.",
  "citation_candidates": [
    "62784212",
